182
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:06,440
<span tts:color="yellow">D'you think Paul takes a lot of care
of his appearance? </span> He's very clean.

183
00:16:06,440 --> 00:16:12,760
<font color="yellow">Hygiene?</font> Yeah.
<font color="yellow">What about clothes?</font> He's more
interested in other things.

184
00:16:12,760 --> 00:16:15,280
He's got quite funny fashion sense.

185
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:20,240
He likes colourful things. <span tts:color="yellow">He does.
</span> He's not, sort of, dowdy,

186
00:16:20,240 --> 00:16:24,480
but he's not interested
in men's fashion at all.

187
00:16:24,480 --> 00:16:31,040
That Telegraph article
said that you convinced him
to abandon the wig. Is that true?

188
00:16:31,040 --> 00:16:35,320
I thought he looked better
without it. <font color="yellow">Did you?</font> Yeah.

189
00:16:35,320 --> 00:16:38,040
<font color="yellow">Would he wear it in bed?</font> Oh, no.

190
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:43,560
Maybe he did before he met me.
You'll have to ask him that one.

191
00:16:43,560 --> 00:16:48,440
That's a good one, isn't it, Louis?
That's made us all laugh.

192
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:55,760
So, he'd be like, "Good night,
Debbie. Let's brush our teeth and
