343
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:36,440
<span tts:color="yellow">Will you do some magic on the show?
No? No.

344
00:30:36,440 --> 00:30:38,800
Not at all.

345
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:43,080
I think you shouldn't cross
that kind of boundary.

346
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:47,560
If they want that,
they should plan that in advance.

347
00:30:47,560 --> 00:30:53,480
Magic should not just be a passing
thing. It should be thought through.

348
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:58,000
Are you ready for a bit of cooking?
<font color="cyan">No, I can't cook.</font>

349
00:30:58,000 --> 00:31:02,840
'From the moment we arrived,
I sensed Paul was out of sorts.'

350
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:07,840
<font color="yellow">Who is Paul up against?</font> Anna Ryder
Richardson from Changing Rooms.

351
00:31:07,840 --> 00:31:11,680
Anna Ryder Richardson, Paul.
It's A-list.

352
00:31:11,680 --> 00:31:17,240
<span tts:color="yellow">..He doesn't know who she is.
..From Changing Rooms. </span> That's good.

353
00:31:17,240 --> 00:31:20,280
Are you gonna do some tricks? <font color="cyan">No.</font>

354
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:22,800
<font color="cyan">I'm Paul Daniels.</font> I'm Anna. Hi.

355
00:31:27,400 --> 00:31:32,240
Hello. <span tts:color="white">This is Chris, our director.
Nice to meet you. </span> Hi, Chris.

356
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:35,480
Er...just shoot me like a football.

357
00:31:35,480 --> 00:31:39,520
OK. Have you seen the programme?
<font color="cyan">No.</font> No.

358
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:43,520
That's where you come through.
<font color="cyan">Who opens them?</font>

359
00:31:43,520 --> 00:31:46,320
A man opens them for you. <font color="cyan">Right.</font>

360
00:31:46,320 --> 00:31:48,840
So you start up here.

361
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:56,560
Pop you in behind.
Your bag'll be in here already.

362
00:31:59,480 --> 00:32:02,400
<font color="cyan">Hmm.</font> Does it look all right, Paul?

363
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:09,960
I'm just curious. Did you not find
that interesting - you push one open
and they both open? <font color="yellow">No.</font>

364
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:17,080
It's got a pulley system.
You're not curious at all, are you?
Must be counterweighted.

365
00:32:17,080 --> 00:32:22,160
